Vodafone Turkey Grows Service Revenue 32% in April Through June

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-07-22T12:23:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-22/vodafone-turkey-grows-service-revenue-32-in-april-through-june.html
Vodafone Group Plc (VOD) ’s  Turkey  unit
increased its service revenue 32 percent to 411 million pounds
($670 million) in April through June as income from voice and
data climbed, the company said.  Vodafone’s Turkish unit, the second-biggest operator in
Turkey, said subscribers rose to 17.5 million at the end of June
from 16.8 million three months earlier, in a statement on its
 website  today. “Customer movement during the quarter comprised
133,000 net losses and a gain of 815,000 due to a change in the
disconnection policy,” it said.  Revenue from data increased 80 percent in the three months
ending June, with data users rising 36 percent to 5.3 million,
the company said.  Vodafone is focusing on “building profitability and
scale” in Turkey, it said. The company competes with Turkcell
Iletisim Hizmetleri AS, the country’s biggest mobile-phone
operator, and Avea Iletisim Hizmetleri AS, a unit of  Turk
Telekomunikasyon AS. (TTKOM)   Average monthly revenue per user increased 23 percent to
19.9 liras ($11.9), the company’s Turkish unit said in an e-
mailed statement.  Vodafone’s Turkish unit increased the weighting of data
revenue to total sales last year to 5.5 percent after investing
in network upgrades, Serpil Timuray, chief executive of the
Turkish division, said on July 15.  The company’s Turkish sales surged 30 percent to 3.7
billion liras in the fiscal year ended March 31, with 29 percent
growth in service revenue, Newbury, England-based Vodafone said
May 17.  To contact the reporter on this story:
